Return a random [r,g,b] color value.

### syntax

~~~ python
random_color()
~~~

### returns

3-element list containing (r,g,b) values between 0.0 and 1.0

### examples


#### draw a random colored cube


<%= vroom_example_image "utils", "random-color", "draw-a-random-colored-cube.png" %>


~~~ python
def display():
   lighting(False)
   color(random_color())
   cube(3.0)
~~~


#### assign random colors to new objects


<%= vroom_example_image "utils", "random-color", "assign-random-colors-to-new-objects.png" %>


~~~ python
def init():
   Global.points = [random_vertex(-5, 5) for _ in range(10)] 
   Global.colors = [random_color() for _ in range(10)]

def display():
   lighting(False)
   for (col, point) in zip(Global.colors, Global.points):
      color(col)
      pushMatrix()
      translate(point)
      sphere(0.5)
      popMatrix()
~~~


